<BlogLayout title="Scrabble Hook Words Guide — S-Hooks, Front-Hooks & Back-Hooks Strategy" description="Master hook words in Scrabble: add one letter to existing words for big scores. Learn S-hooks, front-hooks, back-hooks. Free Scrabble guide. Free tool." keywords="scrabble hook words, s hooks scrabble, front hooks scrabble, back hooks strategy, hooking words scrabble, add letter to word scrabble">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Hook Words Guide — S-Hooks, Front-Hooks & Back-Hooks Strategy","description":"Master hook words in Scrabble: add one letter to existing words for big scores with S-hooks, front-hooks, and back-hooks.","datePublished":"2026-06-30",
    "dateModified": "2026-06-18","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-hook-words-guide"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What are hook words in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Hook words are plays where you add a single letter to the front or back of an existing word on the board to create a new valid word. For example, adding S to RAIN makes RAINS, or adding C to LOSE makes CLOSE. You score both the new letter's word AND the hook extension."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is an S-hook in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"An S-hook is adding S to the end of an existing word to pluralize it (RAIN→RAINS, QUIZ→QUIZZES). It's the most common hook because most nouns and verbs accept S. You score your new word PLUS the re-scored existing word with the S added."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What's the difference between front-hooks and back-hooks?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Front-hooks add a letter before the existing word (C+LOSE=CLOSE, S+LAUGHTER=SLAUGHTER). Back-hooks add after (RAIN+S=RAINS). Front-hooks are rarer and harder to spot, making them more surprising and harder for opponents to block."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 pt-4 pb-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
