      </nav>
      <BlogCrossLinks title="Scrabble Hook Words Guide" />
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Hook Words Guide — One Letter, Big Points</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>6 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔍</span> Solver</a> <a href="/activities/#quiz" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🎯</span> Quiz</a> <a href="/activities/#anagram" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔀</span> Anagram</a> <a href="/activities/#rack" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🎲</span> Rack</a> <a href="/activities/#wotd" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">📖</span> WOTD</a> <a href="/sixty-seconds/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">⏱️</span> 60s</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Hook words are one of Scrabble's most efficient scoring techniques. By adding a single letter to an existing word on the board, you score your new word AND re-score the extended word — all from one tile placement. Mastering S-hooks, front-hooks, and back-hooks can add 20-40 extra points per game.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">3</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Hook Types</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">S</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Most Common Hook</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">2x</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Words Scored Per Play</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">+20-40</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Extra Points Per Game</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">The Three Hook Types</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">S-Hook (Back)</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Add S to pluralize: RAIN→RAINS, WORD→WORDS, TILE→TILES. Works on ~90% of nouns and verbs. The safest and most common hook type.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">Front-Hook</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Add letter before: C+LOSE=CLOSE, S+CREAM=SCREAM, B+REACH=BREACH. Rarer but opponents rarely block the front of words.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20"><p class="text-purple-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">Back-Hook (non-S)</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Add non-S letter after: CHIN+A=CHINA, GRAPH+Y=GRAPHY. Extends words with suffixes: -ED, -ER, -LY, -Y, -D.</p></div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Hook Strategy Tips</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Play perpendicular to existing words:</span> When you hook, your new word runs perpendicular to the existing one. Position your play to hit premium squares with the new word while scoring the hook extension for free.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Save S tiles for hooks:</span> Don't waste S on a basic plural. Hold it until you can hook an existing high-value word while simultaneously playing your own word through a premium square. One S tile, two scoring events.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Memorize surprise front-hooks:</span> B+LOCK, C+LAMP, S+TALK, G+HOST, W+ITCH — these front-hooks catch opponents off-guard because players rarely think about what goes BEFORE a word on the board.</p></div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">S-HOOK</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">plurals</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FRONT</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">add before</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BACK</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">add after</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">2x SCORE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">both words</span></span>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">The best hooks target words sitting near <span class="text-white font-medium">premium squares</span>. If a word sits adjacent to a TWS, hooking it with S while running your new word through that TWS triples your word AND adds the hook. One tile, two scoring events.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
